notes:
ġharīb : 'Foreign, alien;
strange, wonderful; rare, unusual, extraordinary; --poor, destitute;
meek, mild, humble, lowly; --a stranger, foreigner, an alien; --a poor
man; a meek or humble person'. (Platts p.770)

taubah karnā : 'To vow to sin no more; 
    to repent (of evil, sin, crime, &c.); to recant; to abjure, renounce, 
    forswear'. (Platts p.341)

navā : 'Voice, sound; modulation; song; 
    air; --a certain musical tone or mood; riches, opulence, wealth, plenty; subsistence; 
    --prosperity; goodness or splendour of circumstances;--a splendid situation; 
    --a happy life'. (Platts p.1157)

sharīk : 'Sharer, participator, partaker (with); a partner, co-partner, 
    an associate, a colleague, comrade, ally, a confederate, an accomplice, accessory; 
    a member (of a community); a friend'. (Platts p.727)

tapāk : 'Warmth, ardour, fervour, zeal; 
    the anguish of love; solicitude of friendship; love, affection, friendship; 
    apparent cordiality; --affliction, distress, uneasiness, disquietude; consternation; 
    palpitation'. (Platts p.309)

āshnā : 'Acquaintance; friend; associate; 
    intimate friend, familiar; lover, sweetheart; paramour; mistress, concubine; 
    --adj. Acquainted (with, - se ), knowing, known; attached 
  (to), fond (of)'. (Platts p.57)

shikastah : 'Broken; defeated, routed; 
    carried away (by inundation, as river-banks, &c.); reduced to straits; 
    bankrupt; sick; wounded; weak; infirm'. (Platts p.730)

engTranslation:
1) I loved the garden-- but now, there is this 
      [much] irritation--

 2) that from/with a wave of rose-scent, {I am harassed/distressed / 'the breath comes into my nose'}

1) I loved the garden-- but now, there is this 
      [much] irritation--

 2) that from/with a wave of rose-scent, {I am harassed/distressed / 'the breath comes into my nose'}

notes:
dimāġh : 'The brain; head, mind, intellect; 
    spirit; fancy, desire; airs, conceit; pride, haughtiness, arrogance... ; --the 
  organ of smell'. (Platts p.526)

daftar : 'A roll, scroll, list; an index; 
    a bundle of papers or written documents tied together in a cloth; a record, 
    register, journal, book, volume, account-book ... archives; a record-office; 
    an office, counting-house, place of business:'. (Platts p.519)

hoshyārī : 'Sense; prudence; discretion; 
    --carefulness, caution, vigilance, watchfulness, alertness; --sobriety'. (Platts 
    p.1230)

be-navā : 'Without provisions or furniture; 
    without prosperity or splendour in condition; indigent, destitute; ... -- 
    be-navāʾī , s.f. Indigence, destitution, beggary; 
    mendicancy'. (Platts p.204)

ārzū : 'Wish, desire, longing, eagerness; 
    hope; trust; expectation; intention, purpose, object, design; inclination, 
    affection, love'. (Platts p.40)

pahlū : 'A side; flank, wing; a facet; 
    --utility; profit, advantage; indirect or crooked expedient; dishonourable 
  or fraudulent means'. (Platts p.289)

bayāñ : 'Declaration, assertion, affirmation; 
    explanation, exposition, description, relation, disclosure, unfolding, circumstantial 
    indication or evidence; perspicuity, clearness'. (Platts p.205)
